  <h1>
   hspeed
  </h1>
  <span>
   hspeed
  </span>
  is one of the "built in" properties that all instances have and defines the horizontal movement speed (along the x-axis) of the instance in pixels per step. So, an
  <span>
   hspeed
  </span>
  of 3 means 3 pixels of movement to the right
    (+x) every step, and an
  <span>
   hspeed
  </span>
  of -3 would mean 3 pixels of movement to the left (-x) every step.
  
  
   Note that if you set the
  <span>
   <a href="speed.htm">
    speed
   </a>
  </span>
  and/or
  <span>
   <a href="direction.htm">
    direction
   </a>
  </span>
  variables then the
  <span>
   hspeed
  </span>
  value will be updated automatically to
    reflect these changes, and likewise, changing the
  <span>
   hspeed
  </span>
  value will also affect the
  <span>
   speed
  </span>
  and
  <span>
   direction
  </span>
  values. Also note that
  <a href="gravity.htm">
   <span>
    gravity
   </span>
  </a>
  ,
  <a href="gravity_direction.htm">
   <span>
    gravity_direction
   </span>
  </a>
  and
  <a href="friction.htm">
   <span>
    friction
   </span>
  </a>
  can all modify the value of this variable when they are used in your games.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">hspeed;
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a>
(single precision floating point value)
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if keyboard_check(vk_left) hspeed = -5; if keyboard_check(vk_right) hspeed = 5;
</code></pre>
  The above code will change the horizontal speed depending on which keys are pressed.
 </body>
